dge of Newtonian to quantum mechanics and classical to contemporary dance. Including problem sets and choreographic exercises to solidify understanding, this book will be of interest to anyone curious about physics or dance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aDance. 0aPhysics and the arts. 0aPhysics. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / General.2bisacsh1 aDemers, Sarah, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chem., Mat.Sc, Geosc 2019 Englishz978311061064208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry,  Materials Sc, Geosc 2019z9783110606461oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065488240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300240634423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300240634.jpg  a978-3-11-061064-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chem., Mat.Sc, Geosc 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065488-2  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DPCb2019